<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="532" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1487,1981]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1740,1765]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[321,459,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Morphology</emphasis>
: The male color pattern of this species is very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier, 2018" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="2018" box="[1172,1303,1740,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Eumastacidae" genus="Pseudomastax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciollii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1172,1303,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">P. graciollii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1310,1399,1740,1765]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1310,1399,1740,1765]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[265,384,1775,1800]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,193,1956]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudomastax nigroplagiata Descamps, 1970, male from Rio Branco, Acre, Brazil (A and B) and Pseudomastax sp., female from Tabatinga, Amazonas, Brazil (C–E). (A and C) habitus; (D) dorsal view; (B and E) head in frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609382/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Figure 4A</figureCitation>
, but differs by the shape of male cerci and phallic complex (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Descamps" authorityYear="1970" box="[1123,1306,1775,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Eumastacidae" genus="Pseudomastax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroplagiata">
<emphasis box="[1123,1306,1775,1800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">P. nigroplagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the phallic complex is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruner" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[485,620,1812,1836]" class="Insecta" family="Eumastacidae" genus="Pseudomastax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictifrons">
<emphasis box="[485,620,1812,1836]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">P. pictifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[639,749,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">pers. obs.</emphasis>
); see 
<bibRefCitation author="Descamps, M." box="[820,1021,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" pagination="613 - 635" refId="ref6615" refString="Descamps, M. (1970) Revision des Pseudomastacinae (Orthoptera, Eumastacidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 6, 613 - 635." type="journal article" year="1970">Descamps (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, page 632, Fig. 59). This is the first record of this species for 
<collectingCountry box="[454,522,1847,1872]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[541,612,1847,1872]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,415,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,415,1933]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Pseudomastax graciollii sp. nov. (star), Pseudomastax personata (Bolívar, 1881) (triangle) and Pseudomastax nigroplagiata Descamps, 1970 (circle); literature records are in black and new records are in red." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609380/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and the first record of a 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1080,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Eumastacidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Eumastacidae</taxonomicName>
for 
<collectingRegion box="[1134,1188,1848,1872]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Acre</collectingRegion>
State. The examined specimen is more similar to the morphotype occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[800,885,1884,1909]" name="Bolivia" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, according to information provided in 
<bibRefCitation author="Descamps, M." pageId="3" pageNumber="532" pagination="117 - 155" refId="ref6774" refString="Descamps, M. (1979) Eumastacoidea neotropicaux, diagnoses, signalisations, notes biologiques. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 15 (1), 117 - 155." type="journal article" year="1979">Descamps (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, that presents two black marks at the level of the sub-antennal transverse sutures (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1364,1919,1944]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[167,1436,193,1956]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1971]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudomastax nigroplagiata Descamps, 1970, male from Rio Branco, Acre, Brazil (A and B) and Pseudomastax sp., female from Tabatinga, Amazonas, Brazil (C–E). (A and C) habitus; (D) dorsal view; (B and E) head in frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2609382/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). The measurements of the studied specimen are shown in 
<tableCitation box="[740,826,1956,1981]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,152,175]" captionText="TABLE 2. Measurements (mm) of specimens of Pseudomastax nigroplagiata Descamps, 1970, Pseudomastax personata (Bolívar, 1881) and Pseudomastax sp." pageId="3" pageNumber="532">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
